balanceOfBatch(address[],uint256[]).details: See {IERC1155-balanceOfBatch}. Requirements: - `accounts` and `ids` must have the same length.

batchBurn(address,uint256[],uint256[]).details: Burns tokens for each id in _ids

params._from: The address to burn tokens from
params._ids: Array of token ids to burn
params._quantities: Array of the amount to be burned

batchMint(address,uint256[],uint256[],by.details: Mint tokens for each id in _ids

params._data: Data to pass if receiver is contract
params._quantities: Array of amounts of tokens to mint per id
params._to: The address to mint tokens to

burn(address,uint256,uint256).details: Burns amount of a given token id

params._from: The address to burn tokens from

exists(uint256).details: Returns whether the specified token is minted

mint(address,uint256,uint256,bytes).details: Mints some amount of tokens to an address

params._data: Data to pass if receiver is contract
params._to: Address of the future owner of the token

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

paused().details: Return true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

totalSupply(uint256).details: Returns the total quantity for a token ID

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.
